definition: the tens place (or column) in the decimal system
position/location/place/seat/classifier for people (honorific)/classifier for binary bits (e.g. 十六位 16-bit or 2 bytes)/(physics) potential

sentences.english: Just one of those states, West Virginia, is among the top 10 for suicides, ranking No. 8. The only other state in the top 20 was Kentucky at 16th.
sentences.chinese: 這些州中僅有西弗吉尼亞州的自殺率排在前十位。

sentences.english: The computer can multiply two 10-digit numbers in 1/1000 second.
sentences.chinese: 計算機能在千分之一秒內算出兩個十位數數字的乘積。

sentences.english: First see what two tens a number is between.
sentences.chinese: 首先，看看數字是介於哪兩個十位數之間。

sentences.english: MM:There ard dozens of paladins and clerics in this place that can heal me.
sentences.chinese: 在這裏有數十位聖武士和牧師能治療我。

sentences.english: Only three countries have stayed in the top ten for the lowest male death rates all that time.
sentences.chinese: 只有三個國家的男性最低死亡率一直都排在前十位。

sentences.english: In the faithful waiter' s waist exists a list of the ten listeners.
sentences.chinese: 在忠實的侍者的腰裏存有那十位聽衆的名單。

sentences.english: This is a menu of the ten shortest presidencies in US history.
sentences.chinese: 下面就是美國十位任期最短的總統。

sentences.english: Name ten Oscar winners for Best Actor or Actress.
sentences.chinese: 說出十位奧斯卡影帝或影后的名字。

sentences.english: When choosing drinks, apple juice barely makes the top 10.
sentences.chinese: 當選擇飲料的時候，蘋果汁僅在第十位。

sentences.english: By way of vertical calculation , we should start from the ones and then in the tens .
sentences.chinese: 計算應從個位開始加起，然後再算十位。

sentences.english: At number ten and definitely not the least is Giza Pyramid Complex located in Cairo Egypt.
sentences.chinese: 第十位就是位於埃及開羅的吉薩金字塔羣。

sentences.english: Thirty security personnel are released safely in the south wazir is tan region of pakistan.
sentences.chinese: 在巴基斯坦的南瓦齊里斯坦有三十位安全人員獲釋。

sentences.english: This is the first time that any country's reserves have exceeded 10 digits.
sentences.chinese: 這是有史以來第一次一個國家的外匯儲備超過十位數。

sentences.english: Around 30 overseas visitors are due to arrive tomorrow afternoon.
sentences.chinese: 明天下午將有三十位外賓來訪。

sentences.english: At last, there were the best thirty swordsmen attended the final match.
sentences.chinese: 最後選出最精銳的劍客三十位進行決賽。

sentences.english: Then see which ten a number is closer to.
sentences.chinese: 然後再看哪一個十位數最接近你要四捨五入的數字。
